cs.CG, cs.GR, cs.DS, cs.NA, cs.SG. 

This paper deals with computational geometry and topology, specifically the problem of computing the polyhedron corresponding to a given metric. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also involves algorithms for computing shortest paths and Delaunay triangulations, which fall under cs.GR (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of differential equations suggests a numerical analysis component, which could place the paper in cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the study of polyhedral surfaces and their properties could fall under cs.SG (Computer Science and Society).
